  "title": "Alarin",
  "description": "<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Brief</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Campaign Intro</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a33035e-7fff-2eeb-c9ca-9cf091cc9db5\" style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">You may notice that some terms in the campaign brief below are bolded. All of this information is widely known by all people who dwell in this world. The bolded terms are meant to call your attention to areas that may be worth further scrutiny. Most briefs will contain three pieces of information. Clues and hints exist within the names of the information bits and the text itself. Sometimes the end of a piece of information will give a specific ability, spell, quest, etc that is unlocked now that you’ve discovered the brief. This will be written in italics.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">This Is Not A Game</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Alarin is a world of magic and mystery but some things are much easier to assess than on Earth. Native Alarins are aware of their own character sheets, levels, and so on. Many of the natives even have limited abilities to </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Analyze</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> others. Generations of institutional knowledge has led to a solid understanding among even the lowest about common classes and pathways to power. However, despite the fact that there are rules behind every interaction between peoples and the world itself there are many rules and rule systems that are only known to those who have progressed along the paths needed to unlock those paths. Such secrets are often jealously guarded. No one knows the origins of </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The System</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> but it existed before the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Withdrawal</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> and except for the lack of divine powers since that time, has not changed since. As residents of Alarin you have a basic understanding of the rules which underpin your world even if the rules have seldom worked in your favor.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\"> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Inequality Is The Rule</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> Even the land itself rejects any doctrine of fairness. Scattered throughout the world are regions of low and high magic. In the lowest areas, only characters and monsters level one or lower can function normally. All others suffer a debilitating lassitude. Low areas, like the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Emberfields</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> where our campaign begins, support characters from levels 1-3 and magical monsters at a similar power level. In the low areas, magical manifestations are rare unless a </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Manatide</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> rises, bringing a surge of monsters and magic, but also an opportunity for wealth and advancement for those who would normally be chained to those regions for their entire lives. Classes are another example of inequity, most are only able to unlock classes similar to their parents. Two parents with the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Menial</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> class are unlikely to give their child the opportunity to unlock anything greater. Meanwhile, a child of a </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Noble</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> or even a rich </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Merchant</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> would have far more options, even if their family might artificially restrict some of those options.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Risks and Rewards</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> An eternal truth of Alarin is that the greater the wager, the greater the possible return. Should you decide to fight a dragon in its den, scale the icy fjords of </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Grostheim</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">, or defy the dark powers of </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Abaddon</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">, there is no guarantee of success but in the unlikely event you survive, your life will be forever changed. It is this idea that draws many into the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Adventuring Guilds</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">. These guilds give even the poorest a chance to roll the dice and change their fates. Admittedly, most adventurers end up only slightly more successful than chattel slaves or slightly less successful than ground meat. For good or ill, you’ve joined the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Vitastim Guard</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">, signing away years of your lives and a ruinous tax on your earned wealth. After the barest amount of training needed to unlock your classes, they’ve assigned you to a “</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Level 6 Open Contract.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">” This basically means that the owner of your contract paid a sufficient sum to be able to order you into the gates of </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Tartarus</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> and at worst has to pay a moderate death stipend (to the guild, not your family). The contract is owned by a certain </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Jack Horner</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">. Even worse, he somehow only paid a pittance for your service. Possibly because of the oddly short term of service. The contract was only until the 27th of November and you aren’t likely to arrive at the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Horner Farm</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> until the 20th or 21st.</span></p>",
